
[1]byssolite

   BYS'SOLITE,n. [Gr. fine flax, and stone; so called from its resemblance
   to moss.]

   A rare mineral, occurring in very delicate filaments, short, flexible
   and elastic. Their color is olive green, or brownish yellow, and their
   luster a little silky. Jameson places byssolite under actinolite; Hauy
   arranges it under amianthoid.
